Tourism is a diverse indystry whoch offers long-term career opportunities for enthusiastic individuals who whant to put their education and skills to work in various environments. People in tourism may work indoors or outdoors, standard hours or on a flexible schedule, seasonal jobs or all-year-round. It is one of the most exciting and diverse career paths out there. The tourism industry can be divided into five career areas: accommodation, transportation and travel services, food and beverage services, recreation and entertainment.
Types of professions:
Event Planner, ski patrol supervisor, team leader accounting, director of sales and marketing, adventure company owner, Vice President of Human Resources, concierge, cook, sales coordinator, bartender, ski repair technician, attractions operations manager and other.
